# Angular Frontend Rules

Read `ai-context/tech-stack.md` and `ai-context/project-structure.md` for full context.

## Architecture

- Standalone components only (no NgModules for features)
- Feature routes are lazy-loaded in `app.routes.ts`
- State management via Angular Signals (avoid RxJS where signals work)
- Services in `core/api/` handle all HTTP calls

## File Structure

- Feature code goes in `frontend/src/app/features/<feature-name>/`
- Shared UI components go in `frontend/src/app/shared/`
- TypeScript interfaces go in `frontend/src/app/core/models/`
- API services go in `frontend/src/app/core/api/`

## Styling

- Mobile-first responsive design
- SCSS with CSS variables for theming
- No CSS frameworks — custom styles

## Conventions

- One component per file
- Use `inject()` instead of constructor injection
- Use `input()` / `output()` signal-based APIs for component I/O
- Prefix HTTP service methods with the action: `getRatings()`, `updateTask()`, `deleteNote()`
